The paper deals with the uplink of a Massive MIMO network, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The use of random matrix theory also suggests a possible categorization under statistical mechanics (cs.SI). The paper also deals with the optimization of minimum mean-squared error (M-MMSE) processing, which is a topic related to machine learning (cs.MM). Finally, the paper presents a large system analysis, which is a topic related to theoretical computer science (cs.LG).
